{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh vermicelli into it. Cover vermicelli with warm water and set aside to soak for 30 minutes. Drain vermicelli through Varoma dish, transfer to a ceramic or glass bowl (12-14 cm base) and place bowl into Varoma dish, making sure some holes remain unobstructed to allow steam to circulate.","Place garlic cloves and oil into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>4 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>, then sauté <nobr>3 min\/120°C\/speed <\/nobr>.","Add salt, pepper, sugar, soy sauce, rice wine and 200 g of the water and cook <nobr>4 min\/120°C\/speed <\/nobr>. Meanwhile, arrange prawns on top of drained vermicelli.","Pour garlic sauce from mixing bowl over all prawns. Place remaining 500 g water into mixing bowl, insert simmering basket and weigh green beans into it. Place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>20-25 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>, or until prawns are cooked. Remove Varoma, then remove simmering basket with aid of spatula.","Sprinkle spring onions\/shallots over prawns and vermicelli and serve with beans. When serving, mix vermicelli until all are a light brown colour and coated in sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 - 250 g Chinese vermicelli noodles (made from mung beans or rice)","warm water, for soaking","70 g garlic cloves","40 g oil","½ tsp salt              (optional)","¼ tsp ground white pepper","35 g sugar","40 g soy sauce","20 g rice wine","700 g water","200 - 250 g medium raw prawns, peeled and deveined","200 gram green beans","50 g spring onions\/shallots, cut into thin slices (3 mm) or curled (see Tips), for garnishing"]}],"id":"r156320","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-52ztrQoCOhs\/XZMzq1HfpmI\/AAAAAAAAa0A\/n2v7YWgL_Co9JcTFGk4NI50PDXEkAgfpQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_h0kZWiWUFRozjYgn.png","title":"Chinese vermicelli with prawns and garlic sauce","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"16 g","fat":"11 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"66 g","calories":"1832 kJ \/ 438 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass bowl, bowl","hintsAndTricks":["If your shallow bowl is <nobr>14 cm<\/nobr> or larger, ensure the holes of the Varoma dish are not blocked by using a steaming rack, <nobr>2 small<\/nobr> chopsticks or a wooden chopstick broken in two to support the shallow bowl off the bottom of the Varoma dish.<br>- To curl the spring onions, cut into <nobr>10 cm<\/nobr> lengths and then lengthways into thin strips (julienne), place into a bowl of cold water with a few ice cubes and allow to chill approx. <nobr>20-30 minutes<\/nobr> until curled.<br>- If the raw prawns are small <nobr>(6-7 cm)<\/nobr> they can be steamed from frozen."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}